00:20:59.900 --> 00:21:01.990
In merry old England, there
was Robert Hook.

00:21:01.990 --> 00:21:06.120
You know him from Hook's
Law, in mechanics.

00:21:06.120 --> 00:21:09.060
So he was doing military
research in 1660.

00:21:09.060 --> 00:21:11.320
He was trying to understand what
was the optimal way to

00:21:11.320 --> 00:21:13.010
stack cannon balls.

00:21:13.010 --> 00:21:15.160
So when you're on a battle
front, you want to figure out

00:21:15.160 --> 00:21:18.310
how to keep your material
compactly arranged.

00:21:18.310 --> 00:21:21.810
You don't lie them
on the ground.

00:21:21.810 --> 00:21:25.690
So from that, he concluded that
crystal that is a regular

00:21:25.690 --> 00:21:28.560
array must owe its shape
to the packing

00:21:28.560 --> 00:21:30.142
of spherical particles.

00:21:30.142 --> 00:21:31.320
So that's what he was thinking,

00:21:31.320 --> 00:21:31.980
or trying to imagine.

00:21:31.980 --> 00:21:34.410
Remember, Democritus said that
we have these indivisible

00:21:34.410 --> 00:21:37.800
